  "notes": "Marchigiano. Central Italian of the Marche region. Transitional zone: northern Marche is closer to Romagnol (Gallo-Italic), central Marche is Central Italian, southern Marche is closer to the Neapolitan continuum. Reference: central Marche (Macerata). Key features: (1) 7-vowel system. (2) Metaphony in southern varieties. (3) Assimilatory processes (Loporcaro 2009, Avolio 1995).",
